This paper deals with the problem of detecting artificially promoted memes on social media, which involves analyzing network and diffusion patterns, content and sentiment information, timing signals, and user meta-data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SD), Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). Among these, cs.SI and cs.SD are the most likely categories, as they directly deal with social media analysis and information diffusion.
